description:
Hackathon note to Council 2015-10-14:

City staff is developing plans for an “OpenCity Event” scheduled for the first quarter of 2016. We plan to engage the public in the topics of government transparency and open data. We’re excited for the opportunities that this event will create, especially in the engagement of the technical community to participate in s hackathon, focused on the development of technology solution to address a community issue.

A hackathon is a an event where creative people with technical backgrounds come together, form teams around a problem or idea, and collaboratively develop a solution that often results in a website or mobile app. In order to truly tap into the skill and creativity of the hackathon participants, we are being careful not to define the desired solution too narrowly, allowing the freedom for a variety of solutions to be proposed.

Event planning discussions for the hackathon have focused on the development of a mobile-friendly app/website that provides the community with real-time information regarding the location, wait-times, and traffic related to train traffic within Fort Collins. Solutions could take a wide variety of forms, but we are hopeful that one or more will warrant further development and implementation, providing the community with an innovative solution to a shared community challenge.

description:
• City expenses are pulled directly from the City of Fort Collins financial database.
  • Open Book includes data for the City of Fort Collins, the Poudre River Library District, Poudre Fire Authority, and the Downtown Development Authority
  • All expenditures are included, except for: personnel costs (including payroll), transfers and bookkeeping items, information restricted by HIPAA, and other confidential information
  • OpenBook contains a rolling 2 years of expense data and is updated on the 15th of every month to include information for the previous month.
  • Employee earnings dataset: https://opencity.fcgov.com/d/ix3f-8s6j
  • Note that these all figures are non-GAAP, un-audited values
